est%20efforts%2C%20the%20girl%20died.%20Her%20condition%2C%20Amoebic%20meningoencephalitis%2C%20was%20caused%20by%20the%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri%C2%A0amoeba%2C%20a%20rare%20but%20severe%20brain%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EAbout%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri%2C%20the%20brain-eating%20amoeba%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri%20amoeba%20is%20a%20tiny%20organism%20found%20in%20warm%20freshwater%20like%20lakes%20and%20rivers.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20found%20in%20soil%20or%20untreated%20water.%20When%20people%20swim%20or%20dive%20in%20water%20containing%20this%20amoeba%2C%20it%20can%20enter%20their%20bodies%20through%20the%20nose.%20Once%20in%20the%20nasal%20passages%2C%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri%C2%A0can%20travel%20to%20the%20brain%2C%20resulting%20in%20inflammation%20of%20the%20brain%20tissue%20and%C2%A0causing%20a%20severe%20infection%20called%20primary%20amebic%20meningoencephalitis%20(PAM)%2C%20as%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F%C2%A0https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fdiseases%2F24485-brain-eating-amoeba%5C%22%3ECleveland%20Clinic%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20infection%20spreads%20quickly%20and%20can%20be%20deadly%20if%20not%20treated%20right%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EInfections%20by%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri%3A%20Symptoms%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESymptoms%20of%20PAM%20include%20headache%2C%20fever%2C%20nausea%2C%20vomiting%20and%20changes%20in%20mental%20state.%20While%20infections%20from%20this%20amoeba%20are%20rare%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20take%20precautions%20such%20as%20avoiding%20warm%20freshwater%20activities%2C%20using%20nose%20clips%20and%20making%20sure%20water%20sources%20are%20properly%20treated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EInfections%20by%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri%3A%20Treatments%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20not%20found%20any%20effective%20treatments%20for%20PAM%20yet.%20Currently%2C%20doctors%20have%20been%20managing%20the%20disease%20with%20a%20combination%20of%20drugs%2C%20including%20amphotericin%20B%2C%20azithromycin%2C%20fluconazole%2C%20rifampin%2C%20miltefosine%20and%20dexamethasone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Centres%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(CDC)%20states%20that%20most%20people%20with%20PAM%20die%20within%201%20to%2018%20days%20after%20symptoms%20start%20to%20appear.%20People%20infected%20with%20it%20will%20go%20into%20a%20coma%20and%20die%20within%20about%20five%20days%20from%20the%20onset%20of%20symptoms%2C%20the%20centre%C2%A0said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EAre%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri%C2%A0infections%20common%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInfections%20from%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri%C2%A0are%20rare%2C%20with%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20cases%20%E2%80%93%200%20to%208%20%E2%80%93%20reported%20annually.%20In%20recent%20times%2C%20however%2C%20there%20have%20been%20unusual%20instances%20of%20infections%20during%20periods%20of%20intense%20heat%2C%20which%20experts%20say%20is%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20has%20raised%20doubts%20about%20how%20rare%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri%C2%A0infections%20are.%20Some%20people%20have%20antibodies%20to%20the%20amoeba%2C%20meaning%20they%20have%20been%20exposed%20to%20it%20before%20and%20survived.%20Besides%20that%2C%20some%20deaths%20thought%20to%20be%20from%20meningitis%20were%20later%20found%20to%20be%20caused%20by%20Naegleria%C2%A0fowleri.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20interesting%20revelation%20is%20that%20som%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ee%20people%20don't%20get%20infected%2C%20despite%20being%20in%20similar%20situations%20or%20exposed%20to%20similar%20conditions%20as%20those%20who%20do.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716364860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fe4tmjrm8_naegleria-fowleri_625x300_22_May_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhat-is-brain-eating-amoeba-naegleria-fowleri-that-killed-a-5-year-old-girl-in-kerala-5719217%22%2