%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fpaytm-q4-results-loss-widens-to-rs-549-60-cr-revenue-falls-2-6-124052200375_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fpaytm-q4-results-loss-widens-to-rs-549-60-cr-revenue-falls-2-6-124052200375_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stop%20Treating%20AI%20Like%20Humans%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20A%20Tool%26quot%3B%3A%20Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20week%20after%20OpenAI%20unveiled%20a%20personal%20assistant%20that%20can%20laugh%2C%20sing%20and%20speak%20with%20a%20mix%20of%20different%20voices%2C%20the%20company's%20closest%20partner%20offered%20a%20subtly%20different%20view%20for%20how%20people%20should%20engage%20with%20artificial%20intelligence%20tools.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20like%20anthropomorphizing%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Microsoft%20Corp.%20Chief%20Executive%20Officer%20Satya%20Nadella%20told%20Bloomberg%20Television%20on%20Monday%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20using%20verbs%20and%20nouns%20to%20describe%20AI%20that%20are%20typically%20reserved%20for%20people.%20%26quot%3BI%20sort%20of%20believe%20it's%20a%20tool.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENadella's%20remarks%20hint%20at%20an%20ongoing%20debate%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%20over%20how%20much%20to%20humanize%20AI%20services%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20technology%20is%20advancing%20and%20responding%20in%20ways%20that%20appear%20more%20human-like.%20Last%20week%2C%20a%20Google%20executive%20told%20Bloomberg%20that%20while%20it's%20possible%20to%20build%20AI%20tools%20that%20%26quot%3Bshow%20emotion%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20prefers%20to%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20super%20helpful%20and%20super%20useful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20has%20taken%20a%20different%20approach.%20The%20company%20demonstrated%20a%20new%20voice%20assistant%20last%20week%20that%20it%20said%20can%20understand%20emotions%20and%20express%20feelings%20of%20its%20own.%20At%20multiple%20points%20in%20the%20presentation%2C%20the%20AI%20voice%20appeared%20to%20hit%20on%20the%20employee%20using%20the%20tool%20onstage.%20Many%20on%20social%20media%20likened%20the%20feature%20to%20the%20dystopian%20movie%20%26quot%3BHer%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20comparison%20fueled%20by%20one%20particular%20voice%20option%20that%20users%20said%20resembled%20the%20film's%20star%2C%20Scarlett%20Johansson.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJohansson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20given%20to%20NPR%20that%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20reached%20out%20and%20asked%20her%20to%20consider%20voicing%20an%20audio%20chat%20feature.%20According%20to%20Johansson%2C%20Altman%20tried%20to%20pitch%20her%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20she%20could%20%26quot%3Bhelp%20consumers%20to%20feel%20comfortable%20with%20the%20seismic%20shift%20concerning%20humans%20and%20AI.%26quot%3B%20She%20declined%20and%20said%20she%20has%20since%20been%20forced%20to%20hire%20lawyers%20over%20OpenAI's%20decision%20to%20move%20forward%20with%20a%20similar%20sounding%20voice.%20(OpenAI%20has%20since%20taken%20down%20the%20voice%20and%20replaced%20it%20with%20another.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20ChatGPT%20brought%20AI%20into%20the%20mainstream%20consciousness%2C%20tech%20companies%20often%20conferred%20human%20personalities%20onto%20AI%20programs%2C%20usually%20with%20female-coded%20names%20and%20characteristics%2C%20in%20an%20apparent%20effort%20to%20help%20people%20connect%20and%20feel%20comfortable%20with%20the%20technology.%20%C2%A0Nadella's%20Microsoft%20hasn't%20been%20immune%20to%20that%20behavior%20either.%20The%20company%20has%20released%20various%20conversational%20and%20AI%20programs%20over%20the%20years%2C%20including%20Tay%20and%20Cortana%2C%20named%20after%20Halo's%20female-appearing%20AI%20assistant.%20And%20who%20can%20forget%20Bing%20AI's%20rogue%20persona%2C%20Sydney%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20natural%20tendency%20to%20want%20to%20describe%20artificial%20intelligence%20in%20human%20terms%2C%20as%20people%20look%20to%20explain%20the%20math%2C%20numbers%20and%20code%20behind%20the%20software%20in%20ways%20that%20users%20can%20relate%20to%2C%20saying%20things%20like%20AI%20%26quot%3Blearns.%26quot%3B%20That%20temptation%20will%20only%20get%20stronger%20as%20tech%20companies%20release%20more%20capable%20products%20that%20can%20hold%20real-time%20conversations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20interview%2C%20Nadella%20said%20users%20need%20to%20be%20mindful%20that%20the%20abilities%20AI%20software%20displays%20are%20not%20human%20intelligence.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20got%20intelligence%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20give%20it%20that%20moniker%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20same%20intelligence%20that%20I%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20Nadella%20went%20so%20far%20as%20to%20lament%20the%20selection%20of%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bartificial%20intelligence%2C%26quot%3B%20first%20coined%20in%20the%201950s.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20one%20of%20the%20most%20unfortunate%20names%20is%20'artificial%20intelligence'%20-%20I%20wish%20we%20had%20called%20it%20'different%20intelligence%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20I%20have%20my%20intelligence.%20I%20don't%20need%20any%20artificial%20intelligence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENadella%20just%20wants%20the%20AI%20software%20to%20help%20when%20he%20wants%20it.%20%26quot%3BThat's%2C%20I%20think%2C%20the%20ideal%20relationship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716357120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fr8748s9_satya-nadella-bloomberg_625x300_22_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld