Not%20Truthful'%20on%20Missing%20%24533%20Million%2C%20Says%20US%20Judge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20director%20of%20Indian%20tech%20firm%20Think%20%26amp%3B%20Learn%20Pvt%20faces%20financial%20penalties%20for%20defying%20a%20US%20judge's%20order%20to%20find%20out%20where%20the%20troubled%20company%20stashed%20%24533%20million%20that%20jilted%20lenders%20say%20should%20go%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERiju%20Ravindran%2C%20the%20brother%20of%20company%20founder%20Byju%20Raveendran%2C%20not%20only%20failed%20to%20make%20a%20serious%20effort%20to%20find%20out%20what%20happened%20to%20the%20cash%2C%20but%20deceived%20the%20court%2C%20US%20Bankruptcy%20Judge%20John%20Dorsey%20said%20during%20a%20hearing%20Tuesday%20in%20Wilmington%2C%20Delaware.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20conclude%20Mr.%20Ravindran's%20testimony%20is%20not%20truthful%2C%26quot%3B%20Dorsey%20said.%20Ravindran%20either%20knows%20where%20the%20money%20is%20being%20hidden%20and%20won't%20say%2C%20or%20he%20refused%20to%20find%20out%2C%20Dorsey%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20was%20a%20symbolic%20victory%20for%20lenders%2C%20represented%20by%20their%20agent%2C%20Glas%20Trust%2C%20and%20likely%20puts%20only%20limited%20pressure%20on%20Ravindran%20to%20cooperate%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20financial%20penalties.%20Dorsey%20said%20he%20would%20hold%20a%20hearing%20to%20decide%20how%20much%20Ravindran%20must%20pay%20in%20fines%20and%20whether%20the%20businessman%20has%20any%20assets%20subject%20to%20court%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavindran%2C%20his%20brother%20and%20his%20sister-in-law%20are%20the%20only%20directors%20of%20Think%20%26amp%3B%20Learn%2C%20which%20operates%20under%20the%20name%20Byju's%2C%20according%20to%20court%20testimony.%20Dorsey%20has%20repeatedly%20expressed%20frustration%20over%20the%20company's%20refusal%20to%20say%20where%20the%20money%20is%20being%20held.%20Earlier%20this%20year%20the%20judge%20ordered%20the%20arrest%20of%20a%20hedge%20fund%20manager%20who%20helped%20Ravindran%20move%20the%20cash.%20That%20manager%20refused%20a%20court%20order%20to%20reveal%20what%20happened%20to%20the%20money%2C%20Dorsey%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDorsey%20declined%20to%20issue%20an%20arrest%20warrant%20for%20the%20Ravindran%2C%20who%20is%20an%20Indian%20citizen%20currently%20living%20in%20Dubai%2C%20a%20city%20in%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20which%20does%20not%20have%20an%20extradition%20treaty%20with%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20Think%20%26amp%3B%20Learn%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20During%20the%20hearing%2C%20Ravindran's%20attorney%2C%20Sheron%20Korpus%20argued%20that%20his%20client%20did%20everything%20he%20could%20to%20find%20the%20money%2C%20but%20that%20his%20brother%2C%20Byju%20Raveendran%20and%20Byju's%20wife%20claimed%20they%20didn't%20know.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20has%20their%20own%20family%20dynamic%2C%26quot%3B%20Korpus%20told%20the%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20missing%20money%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20a%20fight%20between%20lenders%20owed%20more%20than%20%241.2%20billion%20and%20Think%20%26amp%3B%20Learn.%20The%20two%20sides%20are%20battling%20in%20courts%20in%20Delaware%20and%20New%20York.%20Lenders%20had%20previously%20seized%20control%20of%20a%20holding%20company%20set%20up%20by%20Think%20%26amp%3B%20Learn%20to%20issue%20%241.2%20billion%20in%20debt.%20That%20unit%2C%20Byju's%20Alpha%2C%20is%20now%20in%20bankruptcy%20under%20Dorsey's%20oversight.%20Ravindran%20is%20appealing%20a%20decision%20by%20Delaware's%20Chancery%20Court%20approving%20that%20seizure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20bankruptcy%20case%20is%20BYJU's%20Alpha%20Inc.%2C%2024-10140%2C%20US%20Bankruptcy%20Court%20District%20of%20Delaware%20(Wilmington).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20sy