aring%20in%20Mexico%2C%20and%20the%20scorching%20heat%20is%20causing%20monkeys%20to%20drop%20dead%20from%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUp%20to%2085%20howler%20monkeys%20were%20found%20dead%20in%20Tabasco%20in%20southeast%20Mexico%2C%20where%20temperatures%20this%20week%20are%20forecast%20to%20surpass%20113%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20Reuters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fmexicos-howler-monkeys-dropping-dead-heat-toll-mounts-2024-05-20%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20local%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mantled%20howler%20monkey%2C%20known%20for%20its%20call%2C%20is%20classified%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iucnredlist.org%2Fspecies%2F925%2F17978896%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eendangered%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20International%20Union%20for%20Conservation%20of%20Nature%20Red%20List%2C%20based%20on%20the%20organization's%202020%20assessment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocal%20authorities%20and%20volunteers%20have%20been%20collecting%20the%20bodies%20of%20the%20dead%20primates%20from%20forests.%20To%20help%20the%20remaining%20animals%20survive%20the%20heat%20wave%2C%20they%20have%20also%20put%20buckets%20of%20water%20and%20fruit%20around%20the%20monkey%20habitats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Volunteers%20fill%20buckets%20with%20water%20to%20help%20animals%20amid%20drought%20and%20high%20temperatures%20in%20Buena%20Vista%2C%20Comalcalco%2C%20Mexico%2C%20May%2018%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664d5e1920abc1efe8fc3cc7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVolunteers%20fill%20buckets%20with%20water%20to%20help%20animals%20amid%20drought%20and%20high%20temperatures%20in%20Buena%20Vista%2C%20Comalcalco%2C%20Mexico%2C%20on%20May%2018.%3Cp%3ELuis%20Manuel%20Lopez%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fmexico-heat-wave-howler-monkeys-dying-b99e0570dfb53a2fb7ebe663acecde78%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Associated%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20some%20concerned%20volunteers%20have%20also%20brought%20monkeys%20they%20rescued%20to%20local%20veterinarians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20asked%20for%20help%2C%20they%20asked%20if%20I%20could%20examine%20some%20of%20the%20animals%20they%20had%20in%20their%20truck%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Sergio%20Valenzuela%20told%20the%20AP%20on%20Monday.%20%26quot%3BThey%20said%20they%20didn't%20have%20any%20money%2C%20and%20asked%20if%20I%20could%20do%20it%20for%20free.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20treated%20five%20monkeys%20that%20were%20brought%20to%20him%20by%20volunteers.%20The%20animals%20arrived%20in%20critical%20condition%2C%20dehydrated%20and%20feverish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20veterinarian%20feeds%20a%20young%20howler%20monkey%20rescued%20amid%20extremely%20high%20temperatures%20in%20Tecolutilla%2C%20Tabasco%20state%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Tuesday%2C%20May%2021%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664d5e9920abc1efe8fc3cd1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20veterinarian%20feeds%20a%20young%20howler%20monkey%20rescued%20amid%20extremely%20high%20temperatures%20in%20Tecolutilla%2C%20Tabasco%20state%2C%20Mexico%2C%20on%20May%2021.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FLuis%20Sanchez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20as%20limp%20as%20rags.%20It%20was%20heatstroke%2C%26quot%3B%20Valenzuela%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETabasco's%20Civil%20Protection%20agency%20attributed%20the%20monkey%20deaths%20to%20dehydration%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Reuters%20over%20the%20weekend.%20A%20source%20from%20the%20agency%20also%20confirmed%20to%20the%20outlet%20that%20monkeys%20have%20been%20found%20dead%20in%20three%20municipalities%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWildlife%20biologist%20Gilberto%20Pozo%20told%20the%20AP%20that%20the%20wave%20of%20monkey%20deaths%20started%20around%20May%205%20and%20peaked%20over%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20falling%20out%20of%20the%20trees%20like%20apples%2C%26quot%3B%20Pozo%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20in%20a%20state%20of%20severe%20dehydration%2C%20and%20they%20died%20within%20a%20matter%20of%20minutes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20weakened%20state%2C%20a%20fall%20from%20a%20height%20like%20that%20can%20result%20in%20serious%20injuries%20that%20end%20up%20killing%20the%20primates%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Mexico's%20environment%20ministry%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gob.mx%2Fsemarnat%2Fprensa%2Fse-coordinan-autoridades-para-determinar-la-causa-de-muerte-de-ejemplares-de-vida-silvestre-en-tabasco-y-chiapas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20coordinating%20efforts%20to%20determine%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20monkey%20deaths.%20It%20also%20advised%20residents%20to%20notify%20the%20authorities%20immediately%20if%20they%20encounter%20dead%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20AP%2C%20Mexico's%20ongoing%20heat%20wave%20has%20been%20linked%20to%20the%20deaths%20of%20at%20least%2026%20people%20since%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20May%2C%20record-high%20temperatures%20were%20registered%20in%2010%20cities%20in%20Mexico%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20capital%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fmexico-heat-wave-melts-temperature-records-ten-cities-including-mexico-city-2024-05-10%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20May%209%2C%20the%20temperature%20in%20Mexico%20City%20peaked%20at%2093.7%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-hottest-year-ever-history-climate-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%