ia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-walks-back-remarks-on-birth-control-restrictions%2Famp_articleshow%2F110313371.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-walks-back-remarks-on-birth-control-restrictions%2Famp_articleshow%2F110313371.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20financial%20planner%2C%20and%20there%20are%205%20pieces%20of%20money%20advice%20no%20one%20ever%20wants%20to%20hear%20from%20me%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20offers%20and%20details%20on%20this%20page%20may%20have%20updated%20or%20changed%20since%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%20See%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoney-advice-no-one-wants-to-hear-financial-planner-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaid%20non-client%20promotion%3A%20Affiliate%20links%20for%20the%20products%20on%20this%20page%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting-rating-methodology%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20investing%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222403%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eric%20Roberge%20Headshot%20COMPRESSED%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e8e75990413ab8e1da0fa7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221201%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Eric%20Roberge.%3Cp%3EBeyond%20Your%20Hammock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAs%20a%20financial%20planner%2C%20there's%20certain%20tough%20advice%20my%20clients%20never%20want%20to%20hear.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAdvice%20like%2C%20buy%20less%20house%20%E2%80%94%20and%20don't%20expect%20your%20home%20to%20be%20a%20good%20investment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20told%20to%20save%20more%2C%20either%2C%20or%20to%20stop%20trying%20to%20time%20the%20market.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20know%20how%20adults%20always%20told%20you%20to%20%26quot%3Beat%20your%20veggies%26quot%3B%20and%20greens%20when%20you%20were%20a%20kid%3F%20Well%2C%20that%20nagging%20advice%20doesn't%20necessarily%20stop%20in%20adulthood.%20As%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3Efinancial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I'm%20constantly%20giving%20people%20good%20advice%20they%20don't%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20hear%20this%20kind%20of%20money%20advice.%20But%20those%20who%20do%20listen%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20importantly%2C%20implement%20these%20ideas%20%E2%80%94%20tend%20to%20have%20better%20control%20over%20their%20cash%20flow%2C%20higher%20savings%20rates%2C%20and%20more%20financial%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20not%20like%20it%2C%20but%20much%20like%20eating%20broccoli%20and%20kale%2C%20taking%20it%20in%20is%20often%20for%20your%20own%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Don't%20buy%20so%20much%20house%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBuying%20a%20home%20is%20rarely%20a%20data-driven%20decision.%20It's%20an%20emotional%20one%2C%20and%20for%20good%20reason.%20For%20many%20people%2C%20homeownership%20represents%20stability%2C%20security%2C%20and%20even%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20not%20unimportant%20things%2C%20but%20too%20many%20people%20use%20their%20emotions%20as%20excuses%20to%20ignore%20financial%20reality%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20house%20hunting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESet%20a%20budget%20and%20stick%20to%20it.%20We%20often%20recommend%20keeping%20your%20total%20annual%20housing%20costs%2C%20including%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%3Emortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20payments%2C%20to%20no%20more%20than%2020%25%20of%20your%20gross%20annual%20household%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20helps%20ensure%20you%20retain%20flexibility%20in%20other%20areas%20of%20your%20cash%20flow%20so%20that%20you%20can%20own%20your%20home%20and%20keep%20pursuing%20other%20important%20goals%20or%20have%20money%20available%20for%20your%20other%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20And%20don't%20assume%20your%20house%20is%20a%20good%20investment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20often%20caution%20people%20against%20thinking%20of%20their%20home%20as%20an%20investment.%20Again%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20buying%20is%20a%20bad%20idea%20or%20your%20house%20isn't%20worth%20as%20much%20as%20you%20think%20it%20is.%20But%20an%20investment%20should%20provide%20a%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20single-family%20home%20that%20serves%20as%20your%20primary%20residence%20(and%20does%20not%20provide%20rental%20income)%20may%20be%20an%20excellent%20utility.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20not%20what%20I%20would%20consider%20a%20good%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHome%20values%20do%20tend%20to%20rise%20over%20time%2C%20but%20the%20cost%20of%20ownership%2C%20maintenance%2C%20and%20upkeep%20often%20erode%20most%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bgains%26quot%3B%20you%20might%20see%20when%20just%20looking%20at%20the%20transaction%20of%20buying%20and%20then%20selling%20your%20home%20on%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20reasonable%2C%20real%20return%20on%20single-family%20homes%20runs%20about%202%25.%20That's%20not%20nothing%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20not%20something%20you%20can%20assume%20will%20fund%20your%20full%20retirement%2C%20either%20(especially%20when%20you%20have%20to%20live%20%3Cem%3Esomewhere%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20retired%20or%20not%2C%20and%20most%20people%20put%20the%20equity%20from%20a%20home%20sale%20into%20their%20next%20purchase).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Save%20more%20than%20you%20think%20you%20need%20to%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20really%20important%20to%20me%20that%20I%20help%20my%20clients%20strike%20a%20balance%20between%20enjoying%20their%20lives%20in%20the%20present%20and%20building%20assets%20and%20future%20financial%20security.%20This%20would%20be%20much%20easier%20if%20we%20had%20a%20crystal%20ball%20and%20could%20accurately%20predict%20what%20life%20would%20be%20like%20in%2010%2C%2020%2C%20or%20even%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20know%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudget%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20what%20kinds%20of%20emergencies%20you'd%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20and%20prepare%20accordingly.%20We'd%20also%C2%A0understand%20what%20your%20life%20would%20look%20like%20(including%20how%20long%20it%20would%20be).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20that%20clarity%2C%20it%20would%20be%20possible%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20exactly%20this%20many%20dollars.%20Save%20%3Cem%3Ejust%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20and%20feel%20free%20to%20spend%20the%20rest.%26quot%3B%20That%20is%2C%20obviously%2C%20not%20how%20life%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20solution%3F%20Save%20more%20than%20you%20think%20you%20need%20to%2C%20because%20then%20you%20give%20yourself%20a%20margin%20of%20safety.%20By%20saving%20more%20than%20you%20necessarily%20%3Cem%3Emust%3C%2Fem%3E%20save%20to%20%26quot%3Bbe%20OK%2C%26quot%3B%20you%20can%20better%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHandle%20emergencies%20(a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Ehigh-yield%20savings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20good%20place%20for%20an%20emergency%20fund)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETake%20advantage%20of%20opportunities%20when%20they%20come%20up%20(either%20to%20spend%20on%20an%20unexpected%20trip%2C%20for%20example%2C%20or%20to%20use%20money%20on%20an%20investment%20you%20feel%20passionate%20about)%3C%2Fli%